  "response": "Canada has the highest number of lakes of any country in the world. It is estimated that there are over two million lakes in Canada, which accounts for about 62% of the world's total lakes. The largest and most well-known of these include the Great Lakes, which Canada shares with the United States, and Great Bear Lake and Great Slave Lake in the Northwest Territories. The vast number of lakes in Canada is primarily due to the country's extensive glacial history, which created numerous depressions in the landscape that filled with water.",
